wiki.summary: "Fever" is a song by English singer Dua Lipa and Belgian singer Angèle, included on the digital and French editions of Lipa's second studio album Future Nostalgia. The song was released on 29 October 2020 through Warner Records. Lipa and Angèle began teasing the release of their collaboration on social media on 23 October 2020, exchanging the thermometer emoji back and forth. On 26 October 2020, Lipa formally announced that their collaboration would be called "Fever" and that it was scheduled for a release four days later. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Fever" is a song by English singer Dua Lipa and Belgian singer Angèle, included on the digital and French editions of Lipa's second studio album Future Nostalgia. The song was released on 29 October 2020 through Warner Records. Lipa and Angèle began teasing the release of their collaboration on social media on 23 October 2020, exchanging the thermometer emoji back and forth. On 26 October 2020, Lipa formally announced that their collaboration would be called "Fever" and that it was scheduled for a release four days later. The song marks Angèle's first English-language song. It premiered at 23:00 GMT on 29 October 2020. The song was included in the digital and French editions of Lipa's second studio album Future Nostalgia. Read more on Last.fm.
